#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
vpnctl — OpenVPN client/profile manager for a single OpenVPN server.

Designed to be both a safe CLI and a future web-backend command.
- Generates .ovpn profiles, CCD files and optional hosts .bat.
- Keeps a small SQLite registry of clients and operations.
- Lists current OpenVPN connections from status.log.
- Disables/deletes clients safely by revoking certs and updating CRL.
- Manages ViPNet destination networks used by NAT and route generation.

No third-party Python dependencies.
"""
